As7:Remote control of computers and transferring files using ssh
sudo apt-get install openssh-client openssh-server ssh
important file:
nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
you can change the port and privacy settings
after changing, save and run
sudo /etc/init.d/ssh restart
Generating ssh_keys:
SSH keys allow authentication between two hosts without the need of a password. SSH key authentication uses two keys a private key and a public key.
Step 1:Generate ssh keys
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email@example.com"
eval `ssh-agent -s`
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa
xclip -sel clip < ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
add the ssh key in githhub

